  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "[PERM] Retail Leasing Senior Manager/Manager (Shopping mall)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Partner with the General Manager and Leasing team to develop and execute the mall’s leasing and trade mix strategy.</li><li>Optimize occupancy, revenue, and financial KPIs through effective tenant mix planning and leasing execution.</li><li>Lead lease negotiations, renewals, and leasing administration.</li><li>Source and secure new retail concepts aligned with the mall’s positioning.</li><li>Monitor lease terms, tenancy schedules, and ensure timely, accurate leasing documentation.</li><li>Analyze retail market trends and conduct feasibility or reconfiguration studies to enhance mall performance.</li><li>Prepare leasing budgets, business plans, and management reports.</li><li>Ensure compliance with leasing policies, SOPs, and procedures.</li><li>Build strong tenant relationships and cross-functional collaboration with operations, marketing, and cluster malls.</li><li>Coach and develop the leasing team, fostering strong teamwork and performance.</li><li>Undertake other duties as assigned by management.</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Real Estate, Business, Marketing, Finance, or a related discipline.</li><li>Holds a Real Estate Salesperson license by CEA is a strong advantage</li><li>7–10+ years of relevant retail leasing experience (senior manager level typically 10+ years), preferably in shopping malls or mixed-use developments.</li><li>Strong track record in leasing strategy, tenant mix planning, and revenue optimization.</li><li>Proven experience in lease negotiations, renewals, and tenancy administration.</li><li>Solid understanding of retail market trends, consumer behavior, and tenant performance metrics.</li><li>Ability to source and secure new retail concepts aligned with asset positioning.</li><li>Strong financial acumen, including budgeting, forecasting, and feasibility analysis.</li><li>Proficient in MS Office and leasing management systems.</li></ul><p></p><p>Please state your availability, current and expected salary in the resume.<br /></p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. </p><p>GMP Technologies (S) Pte Ltd   |   EA Licence: 11C3793   |   Eddie Tang |   Registration No: R1221129</p>",
